":null,"footerStyle":null,"title":"Ratings & Reviews","titleArtwork":null,"subtitle":null,"isHorizontal":false,"isHidden":false,"rowsPerColumn":null,"background":{"type":"none"},"contentsMetadata":{"type":"none"},"isPersonalized":false,"shouldFilterApps":false},{"$kind":"Shelf","impressionMetrics":{"fields":{"id":"23","name":"","impressionType":"ratingsDetails","idType":"sequential","impressionIndex":2}},"contentType":"reviews","marker":null,"items":[{"$kind":"Review","id":"12917288271","title":"Catastrophic UI/UX Changes","date":"2025-07-21T06:10:26.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"After the latest update, using the app has become genuinely painful. I’m seriously considering looking for an alternative. First of all, Outline now appears in the CMD+TAB app switcher, which is incredibly annoying. What’s worse, the app icon in this list sometimes shows strange one-pixel white borders. While that might seem minor, the truth is Outline shouldn’t even be in the CMD+TAB rotation. Secondly, clicking the app icon in the menu bar now brings up only one meaningless option: “Open”. Come on — what’s the point of having a menu bar icon then? It used to show a list of servers you could connect to with a single click, which was incredibly convenient. I’m giving it four stars only out of respect and nostalgia for the Outline we once knew.","rating":4,"reviewerName":"Alexey Goldman","dateAuthorText":"* null * · Alexey Goldman","response":{"$kind":"Response","id":"54852132","contents":"Thank you for your request! We will share this with our product team for their consideration.","date":"2025-08-12T04:34:00.000Z","dateText":"* null *"}},{"$kind":"Review","id":"12722999064","title":"good connectivity but previous UI was better","date":"2025-06-01T11:05:47.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"The last 2 updates was great in the aspect of improving connectivity. however, with the last “windowed experience”, the icon on dock is redundant and the previous “click and go” experience was better. please revert the recent UI/UX changes. Thanks guys!","rating":4,"reviewerName":"Light_mohammad","dateAuthorText":"* null * · Light_mohammad","response":{"$kind":"Response","id":"54000305","contents":"Thank you for your request! We will share this with our product team for their consideration.","date":"2025-07-09T00:23:39.000Z","dateText":"* null *"}},{"$kind":"Review","id":"6465877210","title":"Best VPN for China & rest of world","date":"2020-09-25T05:32:42.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"After getting past the setup and if you can follow a few simple technical instructions, this is by far the best VPN client for China.  Easily can get around the Great Firewall and switch servers/locations with a breeze.  You can even setup on 3rd party machines that are not even cloud hosted, for example a simple Raspberry Pi server at home with the proper port forwarding to get a real experience and access local channels, regional-restricted content such as Netflix, etc... highly recommend this client server manager setup.","rating":5,"reviewerName":"otwistero","dateAuthorText":"* null * · otwistero","response":{"$kind":"Response","id":"50005779","contents":"Thank you for your feedback! We’re glad to know that you’ve had a positive experience with Outline.","date":"2025-01-28T19:45:30.000Z","dateText":"* null *"}},{"$kind":"Review","id":"12712213054","title":"I don’t like new movable window experience","date":"2025-05-29T16:15:34.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"I love your app and it was great so far. But I hate this new movable window experience. It was great to just reach the app in the control panel. Please roll it back or at least let users decide how they want to reach the app’s interface. I hope you’ll do it and I will be happy with it again! \n\nAnd thank you for overall app!","rating":5,"reviewerName":"Claire de Lune 11","dateAuthorText":"* null * · Claire de Lune 11","response":{"$kind":"Response","id":"54000138","contents":"Thank you for your request! We will share this with our product team for their consideration.","date":"2025-07-09T00:14:39.000Z","dateText":"* null *"}},{"$kind":"Review","id":"4962608938","title":"Works in China","date":"2019-10-17T23:02:00.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"The setting up bit can be a little confusing, I won't recomen this to somoene who wants a 100% user friendly user product. BUT, if you want reliable VPN in China this is one of the best options out there, better than the big companies like Express or Astrill. The only downside so far for me is that its constantly detected by Netflix. Other than that is a pleasure to use.","rating":5,"reviewerName":"Ladder343","dateAuthorText":"* null * · Ladder343","response":{"$kind":"Response","id":"50005809","contents":"Thank you for your feedback! We’re glad to know that you’ve had a positive experience with Outline.","date":"2025-01-28T19:46:59.000Z","dateText":"* null *"}},{"$kind":"Review","id":"12730222550","title":"Bring Back Control from Control Center","date":"2025-06-03T07:46:18.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"Great app — clean, minimal, does exactly what it should. But the latest update ruined the experience. The floating window is clunky and disruptive; it was much more convenient when accessible directly from the Control Center. I was choosing between VLESS and Outline and went with Outline specifically for its streamlined Control Center integration. Now that advantage is gone — there’s no real difference anymore.","rating":3,"reviewerName":"Maria_Sokolova","dateAuthorText":"* null * · Maria_Sokolova","response":{"$kind":"Response","id":"54000958","contents":"Thank you for your request! We will share this with our product team for their consideration.","date":"2025-07-09T00:37:18.000Z","dateText":"* null *"}},{"$kind":"Review","id":"2382162033","title":"One of the best VPN experience in China","date":"2018-04-04T10:05:06.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"Outline is easy to set up, and operates 